>>>>>>> # Volunteer with us - healthcare professionals
>>>>>>> ### Volunteers are at the heart of our charity, and as a healthcare
professional, there are many ways you can get involved our work.
>>>>>>> As well as providing crucial support for people living with diabetes,
volunteering with us can provide an invaluable insight into the lives of your
>>>>>>> The Council of Healthcare Professionals (CHP) is a multidisciplinary
advisory body whose members inform our work and provide us with feedback on
whether we are meeting the needs of healthcare professionals and people with
>>>>>>> To register your interest in joining the Council, please email
healthcare@diabetes.org.uk. If you would any further information, please call
>>>>>>> Our Type 1 Events give children, young people and families affected by
Type 1 diabetes, time and space to gain confidence, share experiences and
>>>>>>> Volunteering for these events allow you to enhance your professional
practice of Type 1 diabetes management. You'll get to see how your advice has
a life-long impact, ensuring everyone leaves an Event feeling more confident
about living with and managing Type 1 diabetes.
>>>>>>> Our regional offices are involved in various activities for both
healthcare professionals directly and for people with diabetes that rely on
>>>>>>> For example, support might include helping at diabetes awareness days
and fundraising events. There are also opportunities to give talks at Diabetes
>>>>>>> You can get involved in running workshops at local or regional
>>>>>>> In addition, you are welcome to participate in the variety of
>>>>>>> If you would like to get involved locally, please contact your
regional office, who will be very pleased to hear from you.
